   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>2.4.1882 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName>. April 2.
      1882</p>
            <p> I must have put my left foot out of bed first this morning. I began the
      day by upsetting my bath: in my endeavours to mop up the water I let down my
      bedclothes into the mess; I jumped up and hurried to this new scene of action
      and in my endeavours to put the bedclothes out of danger mixed up socks, boots,
      drawers, trousers, shirt, tie, jacket etc. with the bedclothes on the top of my
      bed, when I got to that stage of dressing in which it becomes urgent to put on
      some sort of clothes I tried to get my vest out of the general confusion but
      Alas! I was not to finish dressing quietly my bran new boots which I have never
      yet put on and which I meant to wear today fell into the dirty water which I
      had by this time elaborately mopped up with my sponge. The worst part of the
      whole matter was that being nude I could not call any of the maids into my
      room. My clean shirt was irretrievably lost in the bedclothes so I had to come
      down in a dirty one.</p>
         </div>
